DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);


$a = random(7,12,1);
$b = random(2,6,1);

TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Suppose that
\[ f(x) = $a x - $b \ln(x), \quad x > 0.  \]
$BR

(A) List all critical numbers of \(f\\).
If there are no critical values, enter 'NONE'.
$BR
Critical numbers = \{ans_rule(12)\}
$PAR
EOT

ANS(number_list_cmp( "$b/$a" , strings=>["none"] ));


TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
(B) Use interval notation to indicate where \( f(x) \) is increasing.
$BR
$BBOLD Note: $EBOLD  Use 'INF' for \(\infty\), '-INF' for \(-\infty\), 
and use 'U' for the union symbol.
$BR

Increasing: \{ans_rule(25)\} 

$PAR
EOT

@answers = (interval_cmp("($b/$a,Inf)")); 
ANS(@answers );

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
(C) Use interval notation to indicate where \( f(x) \) is decreasing.
$BR
Decreasing: \{ans_rule(25)\} 
$PAR
EOT

@answers = (interval_cmp("(0,$b/$a)")); 
ANS(@answers );

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

(D) List the \(x\)-coordinates of all local maxima of \(f\).
 If there are no local maxima, enter 'NONE'.
$BR
 \(x\) values of local maxima = \{ans_rule(20)\}

$PAR
EOT

ANS(str_cmp("NONE"));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

(E) List the \(x\)-coordinates of all local minima of \(f\).
If there are no local minima, enter 'NONE'.
$BR
 \(x\) values of local minima = \{ans_rule(20)\}

$PAR
EOT

ANS(number_list_cmp( "$b/$a" , strings=>["none"] ));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

(F) Use interval notation to indicate where \( f(x) \) is concave up.
$BR
Concave up: \{ans_rule(25)\} 
$PAR
EOT

@answers = (interval_cmp("(0,Inf)"));
ANS(@answers );


TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

(G) List the \(x\) values of all inflection points of \(f\). 
If there are no inflection points, enter 'NONE'.
$BR
\(x\) values of inflection points = \{ans_rule(12)\}
$PAR

EOT

ANS(str_cmp("NONE"));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

(H) Use all of the preceding information to sketch a
graph of \(f\).  When you're finished, enter a "1" in the box
below.

$BR
Graph Complete: \{ans_rule(12)\}

$PAR
EOT

@answers = (num_cmp(1) );

ANS(@answers );

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
